       pop-up menus.
     - "It exists, therefore it is.  It works."

@{B}@{U}Keith Halstead:@{UU}@{UB}
@{B}V2.0@{UB} - Bugfix for left-out icons (now only displays 'Cut' and 'Copy' once).
     - Added 'Paste Into' to disk and directory pop-up menus.
     - Added 'Paste As...' and 'Paste Into As...' to rename the file.

@{B}V2.1@{UB} - Locale support, Danish catalog and bugfix for spaces in filenames by
       Michael Skibsted S°rensen <MSS@kob.dk>.
     - Cleaned up code, also now deletes clipboard contents after "cutting".

@{B}V2.2@{UB} - Not released to Aminet.

@{B}V2.3@{UB} - Added 'View Clipboard Contents...' command to lister menus.
     - Added 'Clear Clipboard Contents...' command to lister menus.

@{B}V3.0@{UB} - MULTIPLE FILE/DIR SUPPORT!  Code mostly rewritten.
     - Added progress windows for pasting.
     - German translation by Andreas Mair <amair@gmx.de>.
     - Updated Danish translation by Michael Skibsted S°rensen.

@{B}V3.1@{UB} - Extension to 'View Clipboard Contents...' windows allowing immediate
       pasting or clearing of contents.
     - More information in "About..." window (e.g. translation in use).
     - Now automatically copies or moves icons (one item only).
       (Especially useful in icon mode listers.)
     - Added "Abort" button to progress windows.
     - Full AmigaGuide« documentation.
     - Icons for lister button banks and instructions to set this up.
     - More code optimisations.
     - Swedish translation by Lars Renstr÷m <larrie@ludd.luth.se>.
     - Polish translation by Marcin Or¯owski <carlos@amiga.com.pl>.
     - Finnish translation by Marko Seppõnen <marko.seppanen@wwnet.fi>.
     - Updated German and Danish translations.

@{B}V3.2@{UB} - Spanish translation by Javier de las Rivas <javierdlr@redestb.es>.
     - Norwegian translation by Kolbj°rn Barmen <kolla@nvg.ntnu.no>.
     - New contact email and web-site addresses.

@{B}V3.3@{UB} - French translation by Jean-Marc Mossu <mossujma@easynet.fr>.
     - Catalan translation by Llorenþ Grau <llg@cryogen.com>.
     - Bugfix: problem with pasting multiple files into desktop and "left-out"
       items solved
     - Other small fixes (especially tests for corrupt/empty clipboards)
     - Cut'n'Paste commands added to function editor's internal command list
     - Now displays only the filename in progress indicators (i.e. not the
       whole path)
     - Paste commands removed from menus if clipboard is empty (Magellan II)
     - Small cosmetic changes in some requesters - catalogs updated to reflect
       these (doesn't affect actual translations).
     - Some changes to the documentation regarding compatibility with earlier
       versions of DOpus (before 5.66).

@{B}V3.4@{UB} - Ability to paste links to the original files
     - Ability to paste files/dirs into LZX/LhA/ZIP archives
     - Ability to add items to the clipboard - option to check for items
         already in the clipboard
     - Function in view requester to toggle cut/copy of existing clipboard
     - View requesters now show whether items are cut or copied
     - Second view requester behaviour changed - can also be disabled now
     - Italian translation by Matteo Cavalleri <shiva@mwizard.net>
     - Several user-configurable options to alter Cut'n'Paste's behaviour
     - Added a "Help" button to the "About..." window which will load the
         Cut'n'Paste documentation from DOpus5:Help/CutNPaste.guide
     - "About..." window now shows number of items in the clipboard
     - Icon provided for the updated and improved CutNPaste.guide
     - Included an installer script
     - Automatic cutting/copying of an associated icon from RMB cut/copy/add
         menu is now optional - can enable or disable for all listers, or
         enable just for icon (action) mode listers
     - Updates to documentation and 7/10 catalogs - Catalan, Polish and
         Swedish will be updated in future releases, currently the new strings
         for these languages are in English.  Note that you MUST use the
         catalogs provided in this archive with v3.4.
     - Bugfix for copying "somefile.info" icons without "somefile" in icon mode

  @{I}RELEASE 2:@{UI} Swedish catalog fully updated for V3.4.

  @{I}RELEASE 3:@{UI} Catalan catalog fully updated for V3.4.

  @{I}RELEASE 4:@{UI} Bug-fixed Spanish and French translations - if you use the Spanish
             translation, you MUST download this archive and install the new
             catalog or else the "view" requesters may not work properly.

@{B}V3.5@{UB} - In the @{"future" LINK "FUTURE"}!

@ENDNODE


@NODE "FUTURE" "Cut'n'Paste V3.4 - Future Development"

@{B}FUTURE:@{UB}

Probably not a lot, unless you've got some suggestions that will improve it
without making it too much bigger!

I may add the ability to selectively remove or disable items in the clipboard.

I will also probably change the settings system so you use the installer to
alter settings and they are saved in ENV: rather than embedded in the script.

@ENDNODE
